text: Bathurst County, an electoral district of the Legislative Assembly in the Australian state of New South Wales was created in 1856 and abolished in 1859. __NOTOC__ {| class="wikitable" |- !Election !colspan="2"|Member !Party |- | 1856 | | | John Plunkett | None |- | 1856 by | rowspan="2" | | rowspan="2" |William Suttor | rowspan="2" | None |- | 1858 |} ==Election results== ===1858=== ===1856 by-election=== Having been elected to two seats, John Plunkett chose to resign from Bathurst County in May 1856. ===1856=== == References == Category:New South Wales state electoral results by district
